ViewFinder Honor License v1.0

Copyright (c) 2026 Rob Simon

ViewFinder is source-available and free to read, run, fork, and modify.
It is not quite open source — commercial use carries a royalty, on the
honor system. Here is the whole deal in plain language:

1. FREE USES
   You can use ViewFinder at no cost for:
   - evaluating it,
   - personal and hobby projects,
   - education, teaching, and research,
   - contributing improvements back to this repository.

2. COMMERCIAL USE
   If ViewFinder becomes part of how you or your team deliver paid work
   (client reviews, design handoff, agency or in-house product process),
   you owe a royalty. Suggested: USD $49 per team, per year. If that
   number is wrong for your situation, pay what is fair — the point is
   the gesture, not the invoice.

3. THE HONOR SYSTEM
   There is no license key, telemetry, or enforcement. Nobody is
   checking. To pay the royalty, visit
   https://tryviewfinder.vercel.app/royalty and open a royalty issue on
   the repository (or reach Rob Simon on LinkedIn if you prefer
   privacy) — the author replies with payment details. A note about
   what you are using it for is worth as much as the money.

4. REDISTRIBUTION
   Forks and copies must keep this license and the copyright notice.
   You may not resell ViewFinder itself, or a lightly modified version
   of it, as a product.

5. NO WARRANTY
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND,
   EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF
   MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND
   NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS
   BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN
   ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN
   CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE
   SOFTWARE.
